metadata.name: Refractions #47
metadata.description:
Refractions is a study of frequencies, harmonies and abstract representations of natural phenomena. 

It is an experiment of blending three colors to create integrated textural compositions.


Probabilities;

- 14 compositions with variations.

- 2 background color.

- 19 different base color palette (2 monochrome).

- 2 distinct textures with variations.

-  2 different alpha types; tangential & sinusoidal.

- Different edges.

- Several starting positions and styles (wavy or straight).


Made with p5.js

metadata.name: Almost Vertical Lines #73
metadata.description:
Hundreds of lines move and change their inclination without ever overlapping and only occasionally remaining vertical. The additional perceived movements are generated by the difficulty of completely eliminating the aliasing of almost vertical lines. Small rescaling of the frames makes the configurations and their transformations even more elaborate. 

The movements of all lines and the rescaling of the frames are determined by eight parameters with decimal values. The cycles that are generated can therefore have quite long durations.

Antonio Belluscio (@livinbits)
October 2017 - April 2022

Viewing in fullscreen mode and landscape orientation is recommended.
The algorithm was implemented in p5.js without using shaders.

metadata.name: The Emoji Finder Game üîé #132
metadata.description:
This is a 'Where's Waldo'-like video game(!) that procedurally generates one of seven fun and hectic "biomes" to search through. Find the specified emoji before time runs out to win! 

The seven biomes are: Safari, Ocean, Space, Kitchen, Twitter, Forest, and City. Share your game links with friends! 

Created by Michael Perusse | https://twitter.com/mrperusse

metadata.name: Negative Space #114
metadata.description:
In this piece, special attention is paid to negative space, which is emphasized by simple / bold color palettes.

6 different styles
- Network
- Parachutes
- Flow
- Limbs
- Arcs
- Florals

9 different color palettes
- dark
- light
- yellow
- blue
- red
- green
- blue and yellow
- red and blue
- multi

Press any key to download a hi-res png.

p5.js script with a custom shader. Depending on the settings, it take some time to fully render / draw.

metadata.name: Klimtiche #63
metadata.description:
Inspired by the 'Tree of Life' by Gustav Klimt.
Every bird comes with a default weather setting but all weather is optional.
On the keyboard:
use 's' to make it snow
use 'w' to make wind blow
use 'r' to make it rain
use 'n' to stop the animation and then again to clear all animation. 
Variables are snow intensity, rain intensity, wind speed and palette.
Made in p5.js, every tree / meadow / sky is unique in design.
Two birds is rare.
Monochrome is rare.

metadata.name: Ripples #67
metadata.description:
Ripples - Made by Zoltan Szalay @insgraphizm with P5.js
April 2022, Hungary

Features
--------
7 color themes
Light or Dark background
Number of rings
Detail of noise

Keyboard control
----------------
[f] toggle fullscreen and hide cursor
[space] manually generate new composition
[a] automatically generate new composition
[s] save image

Touchscreen
-----------
Tap left edge to automatically or right edge to manually generate a new composition.
